About Us
HistoryCOMMUNITY INVOLVEMENTAWARDSTHE DRAGAS PROMISE


 
The Dragas Companies is a nationally recognized, award-winning developer of condominium communities and affordable homes in southeastern Virginia. Founded in 1968, the company has developed more than 35 condo communities in Chesapeake and Virginia Beach, helping more than 5,000 owners and their families realize the dream of home ownership.
For close to 50 years, The Dragas Companies has been making home buying possible – and affordable – for first-time homebuyers and others looking for well-built homes in well-planned condominium communities in Hampton Roads. Through the years, Dragas has developed more than 35 award-winning condominium communities in Chesapeake and Virginia Beach. Today, 5,000 Hampton Roads buyers and their families are enjoying the benefits and privileges of home ownership.
As a local builder with a national reputation for quality, you can rest assured that Dragas affordable homes in Virginia Beach and Chesapeake have been built to last – just like our reputation.
When you buy your home from Dragas, we’re with you all the way—even after the closing. Our Warranty Department works closely with new homeowners to ensure that all warranty requests are handled quickly and conveniently.
 


History
Mark & George Dragas
Forty-five years can be forever in the construction industry. In our case, it spans two generations of a local family determined to help others in the community fulfill the American dream of homeownership. Our first company was Dragas Mortgage Company, founded in 1968 by George Dragas, a first generation American and son of Greek immigrants who believed owning a home was part of the American dream. A few years later, George formed a partnership with his brother Mark to develop and build reasonably priced homes and attractive condominium communities in Hampton Roads.
From the start, the Dragas brothers believed that providing value would build their business and their reputation. They were right. The Dragas name became associated with quality and recognized for integrity, innovation and a commitment to excellence—long before “excellence” became just another industry buzzword.
Helen Dragas
Those traditions continue today under a second generation of Dragas leadership. George’s daughter Helen E. Dragas began learning about her family’s emphasis on value at the family dinner table. By the age of 13, Helen had her first “official” position with the company—as marketing agent. During many summers and school breaks Helen visited homeowners door-to-door. Even as a teenager, she knew that understanding the Dragas customer would always be key to the company’s success.
Over the years, Helen has worn many hats in the family business. In 1996, she followed in her father’s footsteps and was named President and Chief Executive Officer. Today, with the benefit of years with the company in many different positions, Helen has fine-tuned the company’s vision and has continued the family tradition of providing value. And she’s done it the way her family always did—by building strong relationships with homeowners, employees, government officials and industry professionals. Under Helen’s leadership, The Dragas Companies has received dozens of civic, government and industry awards, including the prestigious America’s Best Builder award from Builder magazine, one of the nation’s leading housing publications.
 


COMMUNITY INVOLVEMENT
Holiday Toy Drive
‘Twas the season of giving and the ForKids Organization geared up for their annual Holiday Toy Drive. With a goal of reaching hundreds upon hundreds of kids, we once again participated in the annual drive. We hosted collections at our sales centers and corporate office with the hopes of gathering the best games, puzzles and sporting equipment Hampton Roads had to offer. When it was all said and done, we raised an overwhelming amount of toys and gift cards for the homeless children of the ForKids program!
If you’d like to donate or volunteer for the ForKids organization or even lend a hand at their thrift store, Good Mojo, head over to their website to learn how to get involved with this award-winning organization. –December 2016

ForKids Backpack Drive
Each year, the ForKids organization hosts a backpack drive to benefit children returning to school in Hampton Roads. We’re pleased to once again participate in the event and stuff over 50 bookbags! We’re proud to support ForKids in their mission to stop the cycle of homelessness in Hampton Roads! –August 2016

Cycle for Survival: The Race Against Cancer

Cycle for Survival is an indoor stationary spin cycling event and funds raised from this event benefit Rare Cancer Research. A maximum of 8 people per team can reserve 1 bike for a 4-hour duration with each member pedaling for 30 minutes. The Dragas Companies sponsored a bike for this event, and 8 pedaling enthusiasts made up #TeamDragas. The team pedaled away—riding towards the ultimate goal of answers and cures.
ForKids Inc.: Most Successful Art Auction…Ever
The 14th Annual ForKids Art Auction & Casino Night was a huge success! The night was filled with whimsical characters that we’ve grown to love since childhood. Thing 1 and Thing 2, the Grinch, and dozens of Cat in the Hat impersonators filled the Waterside Marriott for the much-anticipated event. The children and volunteers of ForKids, Inc. decked the room in typical Seuss-ical fashion with Truffula Tree centerpieces, popular Seuss books, and Thing 1 and Thing 2-themed bidding paddles. The main event was when the bidding started – trips, parties, cars and kids’ artwork went for thousands of dollars! The eager donors kept their biding paddles up all night! For the third year in a row, The Dragas Companies had the honor of being the title sponsor of the ForKids Art Auction. We’re looking forward to what next year has in store! –March 2015
Dr. Seuss: The Teacher of Practical Life

Today we celebrate the 111th birthday of Dr. Seuss. Dr. Seuss has written 44 children’s book that have been translated into 15 different languages. His witty use of small words and creation of memorable characters has sparked the love of learning in kids around the world. The children of ForKids, Inc. are no different. This year, the organization’s Art Auction & Casino Night will feature artwork made by kids of the program – in a Seuss-ical fashion. For the third year, The Dragas Companies is proud to be the title sponsor of this event. If you’re looking for a fun night for a worthy cause, contact ForKids at 757-622-6400 to reserve your seat!
Making the Season a Little Brighter

After a week of “elf-ing” around, our team came together and stuffed festive toy boxes for the families of ForKids, Inc. Nostalgia settled in as we reminisced on childhood memories made with Easy Bake Ovens, fire trucks, and those green Ninja Turtles. Our hope is that the children of this award-winning organization will one day stand where we stand as they think back on the good times they had with these toys. We are more than pleased to have been a part of the ForKids Holiday Toy Drive. Thank you to everyone who helped us to make this season just a little bit jollier for kids and families around Hampton Roads. It’s not too late to donate toys! There are numerous toy drives taking place throughout Hampton Roads. Contact a local shelter, nonprofit organization, or mentorship program to see how you can help. –December 2014
We Build and Invest in the American Dream
Labor Day is fast approaching and with it comes big yellow buses and huge backpacks on tiny backs. As families across Hampton Roads prepare for the coming school year, the ForKids Organization once again offered us the chance to invest in a child’s education through their annual backpack drive. Without hesitation, the entire Dragas Team came together and stuffed 55 backpacks to the brim! Like our President, Helen Dragas, we understand the power of education and we were thrilled to play a part in the lives of so many youth.
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 

 


 
 


 
 
 
 
 
 
 


